Here’s Jojo Joget with the story.

24
00:01:39.040 --> 00:01:41.520
Yet another variant of taxi service

25
00:01:41.520 --> 00:01:44.520
has entered the saturated
market in Singapore.

26
00:01:44.520 --> 00:01:46.320
A group of local cabbies,

27
00:01:46.320 --> 00:01:48.960
who have been dubbed
“The Un-smart Uncles”,

28
00:01:48.960 --> 00:01:51.400
are now providing a niche taxi service

29
00:01:51.400 --> 00:01:54.320
that is increasingly
garnering a cult following

30
00:01:54.320 --> 00:01:56.560
since starting 2 weeks ago.

31
00:01:57.400 --> 00:02:02.360
The service, which has sparked a larger
anti-smartphone lifestyle movement,

32
00:02:02.360 --> 00:02:05.080
offers customers an immersive vintage

33
00:02:05.080 --> 00:02:08.840
and all-around nostalgic
cab-securing experience.

34
00:02:09.360 --> 00:02:11.840
It was the brainchild of local cabbie,

35
00:02:11.840 --> 00:02:14.480
Nicholas Le Fong, and friends

36
00:02:14.480 --> 00:02:16.520
and some friends
who found themselves

37
00:02:16.520 --> 00:02:18.600
at the shorter end of the stick

38
00:02:18.600 --> 00:02:21.920
as non-smartphone-owning taxi drivers.

39
00:02:21.920 --> 00:02:22.960
Actually,

40
00:02:23.320 --> 00:02:26.920
I’ve considered getting
a smartphone for a long time,

41
00:02:26.920 --> 00:02:28.760
but my wife don’t let me
get the smartphone

42
00:02:28.760 --> 00:02:31.800
because she is scared
I go online and start gambling.

43
00:02:32.800 --> 00:02:36.880
But I tell you, one main reason
that I want to get a smartphone

44
00:02:36.880 --> 00:02:40.320
is because I am always
losing out to all these apps:

45
00:02:40.920 --> 00:02:45.080
Grab, Uber, Graber...don’t know ah.

46
00:02:45.440 --> 00:02:48.320
So many of my friends also
don't have smartphones

47
00:02:48.320 --> 00:02:50.880
because we all have cock-up fingers,

48
00:02:51.160 --> 00:02:53.080
some of us the fingers too fat,

49
00:02:53.080 --> 00:02:54.360
some too skinny,

50
00:02:54.360 --> 00:02:56.000
some the finger always shaking.

51
00:02:56.880 --> 00:02:59.160
We are all old-school chaps

52
00:02:59.160 --> 00:03:01.560
and many of us out there

53
00:03:01.560 --> 00:03:04.320
are losing out because
of this thing, you know.

54
00:03:04.320 --> 00:03:08.480
So one day, I sat down
with my friends, drinking coffee,

55
00:03:08.480 --> 00:03:10.160
we talked about this thing.

56
00:03:10.160 --> 00:03:12.280
We said enough is enough.

57
00:03:12.280 --> 00:03:16.360
We cannot be penalised
just because of our cock-up fingers.

58
00:03:17.800 --> 00:03:20.760
People use all these apps because
they want make a statement,

59
00:03:20.760 --> 00:03:24.720
trying to act cool only,
it’s usually not even cheaper!

60
00:03:25.680 --> 00:03:27.920
So we thought to ourselves,

61
00:03:27.920 --> 00:03:30.960
we must start our own lifestyle brand,

62
00:03:31.840 --> 00:03:34.040
come up with our own pattern!
I show you.

63
00:03:34.560 --> 00:03:35.640
You see?

64
00:03:35.640 --> 00:03:38.040
Nicholas Le Fong and his friends

65
00:03:38.040 --> 00:03:42.640
then started to display their
phone numbers at the back of their cabs

66
00:03:42.640 --> 00:03:46.040
so that customers could personally
call and book them.

67
00:03:46.560 --> 00:03:51.560
This practice grew popular amongst
non-smartphone-using cabbies

68
00:03:51.560 --> 00:03:55.600
and became a big hit with local
hipster millennials

69
00:03:55.600 --> 00:03:59.880
who are relishing the new
“alternative” cab-securing trend.

70
00:04:00.480 --> 00:04:03.000
You see, whenever I make a phone call,

71
00:04:03.000 --> 00:04:04.880
it is really just to hear this tone.

72
00:04:05.960 --> 00:04:07.400
It’s so good, right?

73
00:04:07.400 --> 00:04:10.640
This waiting process is all part of the
experience, you understand.

74
00:04:10.640 --> 00:04:11.800
I love it.

75
00:04:11.800 --> 00:04:12.760
You see,

76
00:04:13.320 --> 00:04:17.800
my friends and I are really into
this “farm-to-table” cabbie concept,

77
00:04:17.800 --> 00:04:21.720
through all this minimal processing
of phone apps and whatnot.

78
00:04:21.720 --> 00:04:24.240
It is a very down-to-earth and
personal approach

79
00:04:24.240 --> 00:04:25.800
that really brings me back to a time

80
00:04:25.800 --> 00:04:29.560
when life was much more relaxed
and down-to-earth.

81
00:04:29.560 --> 00:04:33.920
The movement has even inspired
many followers of the movement

82
00:04:33.920 --> 00:04:36.720
to give up their smartphones for simpler,

83
00:04:36.720 --> 00:04:40.320
more retro 7/11 prepaid phones.

84
00:04:40.320 --> 00:04:44.360
There are also plans to call out
new service features,

85
00:04:44.360 --> 00:04:49.080
such as taxi booking via pagers
for VIP customers

86
00:04:49.080 --> 00:04:51.240
and reserved spots on pavements

87
00:04:51.240 --> 00:04:54.600
for VVIP customers to hail cabs from.

88
00:04:55.240 --> 00:05:00.360
So I really hope I get to
VVVVVVVVVIP status one day.

89
00:05:00.360 --> 00:05:04.240
I mean, I just think it’s a very fulfilling
experience, spiritually, I mean,

90
00:05:04.240 --> 00:05:07.640
to wait at least 10 minutes for a cab
just like in the good old days.

91
00:05:07.960 --> 00:05:09.920
In a way, it is also
a silent protest you know,

92
00:05:09.920 --> 00:05:12.040
against the capitalist modern society,

93
00:05:12.040 --> 00:05:13.680
where they are constantly telling you,

94
00:05:13.680 --> 00:05:15.640
they want more of this,
and more of that,

95
00:05:15.640 --> 00:05:16.720
more of this, more of that.

96
00:05:16.720 --> 00:05:18.280
Quicker, faster!

97
00:05:21.200 --> 00:05:23.680
Honestly, at the end of the day,

98
00:05:23.680 --> 00:05:26.000
it’s all about being grateful,

99
00:05:26.520 --> 00:05:31.040
and embracing “less is more”.

100
00:05:32.840 --> 00:05:35.000
But isn’t that an iPhone 7?

101
00:05:36.120 --> 00:05:40.080
Yes, but I also have
2 vintage 2004 Nokias.

102
00:05:40.080 --> 00:05:43.920
Those who are interested in
becoming a part of the community

103
00:05:43.920 --> 00:05:47.560
should delete all taxi apps
from one’s phone,

104
00:05:47.560 --> 00:05:49.000
and then hit the curb

105
00:05:49.000 --> 00:05:52.880
in search of an elusive, un-smart taxi.

106
00:05:53.120 --> 00:05:54.600
Reporting for The Noose,

107
00:05:54.600 --> 00:05:57.040
this is Jojo Joget.

108
00:05:57.040 --> 00:06:01.000
I have no idea why they’re called
smartphones…

109
00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:05.280
if anything, they seem to be making
people more stupid by the day.

110
00:06:05.480 --> 00:06:07.320
Speaking of "stupid",

111
00:06:07.320 --> 00:06:11.600
it seems Singaporeans aren’t just
capable of appreciating good things

112
00:06:11.600 --> 00:06:13.680
created by their fellow countrymen.

113
00:06:13.680 --> 00:06:16.480
It seems that if you
want to make it in Singapore,

114
00:06:16.480 --> 00:06:19.880
you have to be a success overseas first.

115
00:06:20.120 --> 00:06:25.120
Our reporter, Jacques Ooi,
recently met one such fashion designer.

116
00:06:25.560 --> 00:06:27.560
When she was in primary school,

117
00:06:27.560 --> 00:06:31.080
Juraidah Amin’s teachers
never failed to say this

118
00:06:31.080 --> 00:06:33.520
every year in her report book…

119
00:06:33.520 --> 00:06:35.640
She is a dreamer.

120
00:06:36.360 --> 00:06:38.920
I mean, what kind of a remark is

121
00:06:38.920 --> 00:06:40.720
“She’s a day dreamer”?

122
00:06:40.720 --> 00:06:43.000
Did they mean I was an idealist?

123
00:06:43.000 --> 00:06:47.000
Or did they mean to say that
I was day dreaming too much?

124
00:06:47.000 --> 00:06:50.080
Maybe those teachers should have
made their classes more interesting.

125
00:06:50.360 --> 00:06:52.480
Fortunately for Juraidah,

126
00:06:52.480 --> 00:06:55.560
rather than take that
comment as a negative,

127
00:06:55.560 --> 00:06:59.920
her parents encouraged their
only daughter to follow her dreams.

128
00:06:59.920 --> 00:07:03.480
Which she did, pursuing a course
in fashion design

129
00:07:03.480 --> 00:07:05.360
after finishing the 'O' levels.

130
00:07:05.760 --> 00:07:07.680
But for many creative types,

131
00:07:07.680 --> 00:07:11.560
trying to find acceptance
and an audience for their work

132
00:07:11.560 --> 00:07:14.800
proved to be more difficult
than she imagined.

133
00:07:14.800 --> 00:07:17.760
But after 4 years of
dogged perseverance,

134
00:07:17.760 --> 00:07:19.880
she finally hit pay dirt.

135
00:07:20.360 --> 00:07:23.280
A London-based fashion designer
saw a couple of my designs

136
00:07:23.280 --> 00:07:25.080
and offered me a job.

137
00:07:25.400 --> 00:07:27.560
After 2 years of mentoring me,

138
00:07:27.560 --> 00:07:31.600
he helped me with the launch of my
own clothing line called "JUAM".

139
00:07:33.240 --> 00:07:37.000
Because "JUraidah AMin"...so, JUAM.

140
00:07:37.320 --> 00:07:39.040
Everybody thought it was Spanish

141
00:07:39.040 --> 00:07:41.440
and I also kept a low profile,

142
00:07:41.440 --> 00:07:44.120
and just let the clothes
speak for themselves.

143
00:07:44.120 --> 00:07:46.520
The label had a cult following in Europe.

144
00:07:47.560 --> 00:07:50.720
So then, after a while,
I decided to try my luck

145
00:07:50.720 --> 00:07:53.280
back in Singapore
by opening a small boutique.

146
00:07:54.320 --> 00:07:56.720
And rich Singaporeans
fell in love with it,

147
00:07:56.720 --> 00:07:59.400
paying thousands of dollars
for my own dresses.

148
00:08:00.040 --> 00:08:02.920
But with the brand
enjoying wild success,

149
00:08:02.920 --> 00:08:05.800
the press began to ask
questions, such as,

150
00:08:05.800 --> 00:08:08.880
who is behind the success of the label?

151
00:08:08.880 --> 00:08:13.520
When Juraidah finally relented and
did an interview to tell her story,

152
00:08:13.520 --> 00:08:15.840
her sales in Singapore plummeted.

153
00:08:16.280 --> 00:08:18.080
They said, “Why should I pay so much

154
00:08:18.080 --> 00:08:20.080
for something made by a local person?”

155
00:08:20.600 --> 00:08:23.120
My sales plunged by 90 percent.

156
00:08:23.120 --> 00:08:24.440
I even had to close down my boutique

157
00:08:24.440 --> 00:08:26.560
because I couldn’t afford
the rental anymore.

158
00:08:27.000 --> 00:08:31.360
Now, I only have a tiny rack of clothes
in this residential area.

159
00:08:33.760 --> 00:08:36.600
Some say it’s unfair
to paint Singaporeans

160
00:08:36.600 --> 00:08:39.800
as a bunch of snobs
who don’t support local talent,

161
00:08:40.360 --> 00:08:41.680
but it's true, isn’t it?

162
00:08:42.240 --> 00:08:45.240
They point to other home-grown labels

163
00:08:45.240 --> 00:08:47.880
that have enjoyed tremendous success.

164
00:08:47.880 --> 00:08:49.800
So...what gives?

165
00:08:51.520 --> 00:08:53.680
I would attribute this attitude

166
00:08:53.680 --> 00:08:56.520
of all things foreign being good

167
00:08:56.520 --> 00:08:58.960
to globalisation.

168
00:09:00.120 --> 00:09:03.680
You can see this manifest itself
here in Singapore,

169
00:09:03.680 --> 00:09:05.360
in terms of food.

170
00:09:05.960 --> 00:09:10.040
You know, people don’t mind going to
a mid-tier, but crappy restaurant,

171
00:09:10.040 --> 00:09:14.080
and paying $15 for a “pasta”

172
00:09:14.080 --> 00:09:16.360
that has nothing else but

173
00:09:17.000 --> 00:09:20.560
tomato puree and minced beef.

174
00:09:21.240 --> 00:09:25.400
But then, look at the hawker who sells
<i>bak chor mee (minced meat noodle);

175
00:09:26.040 --> 00:09:29.240
it has two times the ingredients

176
00:09:29.240 --> 00:09:33.640
and requires five times
the amount of skill.

177
00:09:33.640 --> 00:09:38.440
Yet when this hawker wants to
increase prices by 50 cents,

178
00:09:38.440 --> 00:09:40.360
everybody screams murder!

179
00:09:41.040 --> 00:09:43.080
It’s so tragic.

180
00:09:43.880 --> 00:09:46.160
Everyone just KPKB.

181
00:09:47.560 --> 00:09:48.880
And there you have it.

182
00:09:49.120 --> 00:09:50.560
This is Jacques Ooi

183
00:09:50.560 --> 00:09:52.200
reporting for The Noose.

184
00:09:53.240 --> 00:09:54.720
Time for a quick breather.

185
00:09:55.360 --> 00:09:56.200
Coming up…

186
00:09:56.200 --> 00:09:59.720
hipsters unveil a new line-up
of zodiac animals

187
00:09:59.720 --> 00:10:02.000
to bring Chinese New Year

188
00:10:02.000 --> 00:10:04.080
into the 21st century.

189
00:10:21.400 --> 00:10:22.400
Stop it.

190
00:10:22.840 --> 00:10:24.760
Hello and welcome back to The Noose.

191
00:10:25.080 --> 00:10:28.440
We’re just two weeks away
from the Lunar New Year,

192
00:10:28.440 --> 00:10:32.440
but many young Singaporeans are
already groaning about the prospect

193
00:10:32.440 --> 00:10:34.440
of having to wear something red

194
00:10:34.440 --> 00:10:38.280
and going through the motions
of celebrating the festivities.

195
00:10:39.000 --> 00:10:42.400
In a bid to modernise
the Lunar New Year celebrations,

196
00:10:42.400 --> 00:10:43.880
the Board of Cultural Management

197
00:10:43.880 --> 00:10:46.120
has come up with
several recommendations,

198
00:10:46.120 --> 00:10:50.240
including a new roster of zodiac animals.

199
00:10:50.640 --> 00:10:52.960
Here’s Andre Chichak with the story.

200
00:10:52.960 --> 00:10:54.840
<i>Gong xi ah gong xi,</i>
(Congratulations ah congratulations)

201
00:10:54.840 --> 00:10:56.880
<i>fa ya fa da chai</i>
(Let’s prosper with lots of money)

202
00:10:56.880 --> 00:11:00.440
Common lyrics to an often-played
Chinese New Year song

203
00:11:00.440 --> 00:11:02.600
that can be heard all over Singapore

204
00:11:02.600 --> 00:11:04.600
from posh shopping centres

205
00:11:04.600 --> 00:11:07.440
to heartland malls,
and even on the radio.

206
00:11:08.120 --> 00:11:11.080
While the older generation
sees these festive tunes

207
00:11:11.080 --> 00:11:14.800
as an uplifting sign that Chinese
New Year is just around the corner,

208
00:11:14.800 --> 00:11:18.720
many young Singaporeans do not
share their enthusiasm for the holiday.

209
00:11:19.480 --> 00:11:20.920
Well, you know what I’m saying?
Like, you know,

210
00:11:20.920 --> 00:11:25.320
like red totally clashes horrendously
with like my skin-tone,

211
00:11:25.320 --> 00:11:26.720
you know, what I’m saying?

212
00:11:27.800 --> 00:11:31.600
Like, everything about this holiday
is totally like red,

213
00:11:31.600 --> 00:11:32.240
you know what I’m saying?

214
00:11:32.240 --> 00:11:35.240
Like, you know,
like the clothes are like red,

215
00:11:35.240 --> 00:11:38.080
like the decorations are like totally red.

216
00:11:38.720 --> 00:11:40.160
Even like, you know,

217
00:11:40.600 --> 00:11:43.480
the money envelopes...
they are like red,

218
00:11:44.200 --> 00:11:46.120
you know what I’m saying, right?

219
00:11:46.560 --> 00:11:48.200
It totally doesn’t even match

220
00:11:48.200 --> 00:11:50.680
the blue notes you are
supposed to get in it.

221
00:11:51.200 --> 00:11:53.080
Right, you know what I’m saying?

222
00:11:54.760 --> 00:11:57.280
I hate my relatives.

223
00:11:58.120 --> 00:12:02.080
In a bid to appeal to millennials
and prevent traditions from dying out,

224
00:12:02.080 --> 00:12:04.720
the Board of Cultural Management
or BOCUM

225
00:12:04.720 --> 00:12:06.480
has put together a taskforce

226
00:12:06.480 --> 00:12:10.520
of well-known social media
personalities and hipster influencers

227
00:12:10.520 --> 00:12:12.600
to make CNY cool again.

228
00:12:13.360 --> 00:12:17.560
The Creative Taskforce of Influencers
aims to make Chinese New Year

229
00:12:17.560 --> 00:12:21.280
a more relatable festival for
young Singaporeans.

230
00:12:21.280 --> 00:12:24.040
After countless meetings
over artisanal coffee,

231
00:12:24.040 --> 00:12:25.640
we’ve come to the conclusion

232
00:12:25.640 --> 00:12:28.440
that the holiday needs
a major overhaul.

233
00:12:28.440 --> 00:12:31.440
For example, red...out,

234
00:12:31.440 --> 00:12:33.200
Rose Quartz is in.

235
00:12:33.200 --> 00:12:35.720
Lion dance...out,

236
00:12:35.720 --> 00:12:37.840
Internet cat dance is in.

237
00:12:38.400 --> 00:12:42.080
But the pièce de résistance
of the entire plan

238
00:12:42.080 --> 00:12:44.520
is to revamp the 12 zodiac signs,

239
00:12:44.520 --> 00:12:46.760
because, come on, let’s face it,

240
00:12:46.760 --> 00:12:49.920
the basic animals are just so lame.

241
00:12:50.360 --> 00:12:53.280
The 12 new proposed animals
for the zodiac are

242
00:12:53.280 --> 00:12:54.160
Cat,

243
00:12:54.160 --> 00:12:55.040
Owl,

244
00:12:55.040 --> 00:12:56.040
Hedgehog,

245
00:12:56.040 --> 00:12:57.320
Fennec Fox,

246
00:12:57.320 --> 00:12:58.480
Koala Bear,

247
00:12:58.480 --> 00:12:59.520
Panda Bear,

248
00:12:59.520 --> 00:13:00.520
Penguin,

249
00:13:00.520 --> 00:13:01.600
Alpaca,

250
00:13:01.600 --> 00:13:02.720
Guinea Pig,

251
00:13:02.720 --> 00:13:03.920
Slow Loris,

252
00:13:03.920 --> 00:13:04.920
Sloth,

253
00:13:04.920 --> 00:13:07.280
and as a tribute to the Bishan 10,

254
00:13:07.280 --> 00:13:08.320
Otter.

255
